Text.Value: Not yet.
What can I say? Adventuring suits me.
Of course.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: Because my life isn't yours to throw away. You had no right to ask that of me.
The future of magic rests on your shoulders, Gale of Waterdeep.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost like a 'knighting' vibe - she's declaring her faith in him, and believes he can do this.

Text.Value: Because I am a god.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: This is one lady love you perhaps do not want to keep waiting, wizard.
It is not my place to destroy another god's creation, however temporarily he joined the pantheon.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of frustration that this is the case

Text.Value: You unleashed something that would consume all magic in existence, and yet you thought only of preserving yourself.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Am I wrong?'. Referring back to Gale unleashing the orb, and then coming to Mystra to ask her to cure him of it.

Text.Value: Well somebody had to. You weren't exactly forthcoming with any offers of help.
You were already worthy. What you lacked was patience, and it cost you dearly.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of gentleness - recognising some of Gale's pain

Text.Value: Your goddess awaits. Hear her out, but remember that you do not owe her obedience, and you certainly do not owe her your life.
That it entered your body and consumed no more than your powers was a miracle. But we will not be granted another.

EditorData.NodeContext: A hint of anger here - Gale's selfishness is not her own, he's pissing her off by accusing her of these motives. The 'miracle' is that Gale didn't do any more damage, not that he survived. Sense of foreboding on the last sentence.

Text.Value: You break up with me, cut me off from the Weave, leave me to die, and that's all you have to say? 'You look well'?
I didn't come for small talk. Why did you summon me?
It is a corrupted, half-born magic wrought in the brief moment Karsus ascended to godhood. It hungers for power just as he did, and it can never be sated.

EditorData.NodeContext: Weighty/strong sentiment here - the Karsite Weave is an abomination in her eyes

Text.Value: When the Karsite Weave entered your body, your gifts were the first thing it consumed.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of gentleness - recognising some of Gale's pain

Text.Value: Fear? An 'unambitious emotion', you once told me. Have you changed after all?

EditorData.NodeContext: Reminding Gale of his former hubris. Not yet ready to believe he's changed.

Text.Value: I was a danger to you. What I did, or rather, attempted to do, was reckless.
Is that why you lied to me about the Crown of Karsus? Self-preservation?
There is much unsaid between us, but time runs ever short.

EditorData.NodeContext: "much unsaid' carries a lot of weight - could refer to their relationship, their breakup, Gale's betrayal etc. Mystra is subtly keeping control of the conversation.

Text.Value: Our relationship bored you. The orb was just an excuse to end it.
I hoped hindsight would help you see what you could not perceive before. Do you understand why I severed our connection?

EditorData.NodeContext: Containing her emotions, probing to see if Gale can be trusted with her next request

Text.Value: I will hear your case.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: Perform this service, and I will see you cured. You will be forgiven.

EditorData.NodeContext: Key info for players - this is the first time they've been offered a cure,

Text.Value: I promise you - it is a burden you are strong enough to bear.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost like a 'knighting' vibe - she's declaring her faith in him, and believes he can do this.

Text.Value: *There she stands. Mystra. Your goddess. Your lover. Your past. And no ordinary idol.*
Reach out. Go to Mystra.
I've been watching your journey here. Your triumphs. Your temptations. Your doubts.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referring to the player's epic journey so far. They may have sensed Mystra's presence at an earlier point in the game, and been tempted to use evil magic she forbids her followers to use. They may also have spoken of their faltering faith in Mystra, but she has no interest in judging them for it now.

Text.Value: *Just as Elminster promised, you stand before no ordinary idol.*
I won't let you down again. When the Absolute is vanquished, I will surrender Karsus' powers to you. You have my word.
Thank you. May the Weave's light guide your purpose, and its wisdom guide your hand.

EditorData.NodeContext: A blessing - Mystra relieved you'll do it

Text.Value: I didn't want to die. And when I saw the Crown, I thought I might not have to, if I only understood its power.
The Weave cannot be lost because we are unwilling to cause a ripple. And that is what is at stake.

EditorData.NodeContext: Matter of fact, not interested in these kinds of specifics. 'The Weave' = magic.

Text.Value: I did no such thing, Gale.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight confusion - she didn't know this was his assumption

Text.Value: So that's what you're scared of. The magic within me is one you can't control. But with the Crown of Karsus, I could.
*Something in the air grows colder. Sharper. Mystra's patience is extensive, but not infinite. She will not wait forever.*
Tactful as ever. But now it is only your candour I require.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Tactful' referring just to how he's handling the situation with dignity. Mystra in control of the conversation.

Text.Value: I don't need your forgiveness. The Crown of Karsus will be mine, and the Karsite Weave will obey me.
Should the odds feel too great, and the orb prove your best hope, call on me in those final moments and I will ensure those close to you are safe.

EditorData.NodeContext: Key info - this gives the player the chance to save their companions before blowing up the brain. A sincere promise from Mystra.

Text.Value: *How many times have you dreamed of this moment? An audience with the goddess who loved you. Who abandoned you. All you have to do is reach for it...*
I have no need of excuses. Nonetheless, you gave me one I had no choice but to act upon.

EditorData.NodeContext: Matter of fact regarding Gale's explanation. The 'excuse' he gave was the orb, she's about to explain.

Text.Value: You were many things to me, but never a threat. And never a saviour.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sharper, almost a warning - don't entertain such thoughts, Gale. You won't like where they lead.

Text.Value: You can do this, Gale. And I'll be right here when you're done.
*Just as Elminster promised, Gale stands before no ordinary idol.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gale looks up at Mystra's statue, his face unreadable
Gale reaches a hand out in front of him, closes his eyes. A brilliant flash of white light and - he's in the Outer planes. Before him, Mystra in her celestial form.

Text.Value: You discovered what lies at the Heart of the Absolute - the Crown of Karsus - and you disobeyed my instruction. Why?

EditorData.NodeContext: Big question - this was the quest Mystra gave to the player in Act 2, which they refused to complete. Mystra containing her frustration, but needs to know the answer. 'Heart of the Absolute' was the term used for what turned out to be the brain/Crown

Text.Value: So be it. Follow the needle of your own wisdom. We shall see how truly it leads you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral - not impressed he hasn't outright agreed to what she asked, but willing to give him the time he needs.

Text.Value: I know. Your union is one I find surprising, but you are your own man and it is not the worst choice you have made, after all.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not news to Mystra. Partner could be any origin/custom player so it's intentionally generic. 'Worst choice' alluding to how he got the orb in his chest.

Text.Value: Goodbye.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: You abandoned me in my hour of greatest need. I had no obligation to help you in yours.
I didn't call on you to make small talk. You owe me an explanation.
The fragment of magic you tried to return to me was not of my creation. It was the Karsite Weave.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Fragment of magic' referring to the orb in Gale's chest. 'Karsite Weave' with distaste - the creation of someone she hates

Text.Value: *There she stands. Mystra. Gale's goddess. His lover. His past. And no ordinary idol.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gale looks up at Mystra's statue, his face unreadable

Text.Value: My concern was the preservation of everything. The Karsite Weave could tear apart the very fabric of the Material Plane.

EditorData.NodeContext: A hint of anger here - Gale's selfishness is not her own, he's pissing her off by accusing her of these motives

Text.Value: Gale of Waterdeep. You look well.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not giving much away - both a pleasantry on an awkward reunion with her ex, and carrying the added implication of the fact Mystra told Gale to blow himself up, yet he stands before her, alive and well

Text.Value: Your goddess calls. Serve her or denounce her as you will - but you cannot ignore her.
Mystra. I never thought we'd speak again like this. Why am I here?
We will find out.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mystra's form disappears. Gale stands in an ordinary temple before an ordinary statue once more. Mystra's idol gazes on, revealing nothing. Gale smiles to himself.

Text.Value: *Beneath the silent stone surges a relentless current of purest Weave. A summoning channel, the kind commanded by Mystra herself.*
I never intended to do harm. Only to prove myself worthy of you.
As do you. But I assume we're not here solely to exchange compliments. So, why am I here?
You were threatened. You realised you couldn't control me.
I don't know. I need time to think.
Go on, my good man - your goddess awaits. Let us pray that good wisdom prevails.
*All he has to do is reach for it...*
And you look radiant.
No wizard worth their hat would destroy such a powerful artefact without first understanding it.
If this is the course you choose, Elysium will be waiting.

EditorData.NodeContext: A promise. 'Elysium' being heaven/where Mystra resides

Text.Value: Never.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: You're the mother of all magic, the Weave incarnate. Can't you just destroy the Crown yourself?
You were my lover, my Chosen, yet still you know so little of me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of disappointment - even after all the advantages I gave you, you can't see further than your own nose

Text.Value: Because I disobeyed you. You punished me for it.
You still believe yourself to be so wronged? You always were stubborn.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of an eyebrow raise - is this a sign of Gale's same old hubris?

Text.Value: Crown yourself, Gale Dekarios, and you will learn what it is to carry such weight upon your shoulders.

EditorData.NodeContext: An icy edge entering her voice - a hint at the challenge Gale will face if he pursues this course

Text.Value: I will not be defied.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: The only reason the 'orb' sleeps is because I have allowed it to feed on the true Weave - a temporary measure, but one that will not be enough to save us.

EditorData.NodeContext: "This is what your foolishness has cost". New information for the player, who believes Mystra simply waved her hand and fixed them because it suited her.

Text.Value: That can't be. It wasn't - it couldn't have been. I only wished to prove myself worthy. I had no idea...
It must be you, Gale. You are the one who carries Karsus' power within you. You are the only one who can.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of frustration that this is the case

Text.Value: I let you down. I was a fool, and fools don't deserve the love of a goddess.
The past cannot be undone with self-pity, nor can a future be forged. Only with the truth will you see the way ahead.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not letting him off easily

Text.Value: How so? You think I should have cured you? Erased the consequences of your actions?

EditorData.NodeContext: Not impressed at Gale's characterisation of his actions and her response, but not rising to it. She's about to correct him.

Text.Value: Not happening. When I get my hands on that Crown, I'm going to wield it. Karsus' powers will be mine.
You can no more control the Karsite Weave than a weather vane could control a storm.

EditorData.NodeContext: A personal warning for Gale, but not specifically that 'he' couldn't control it - no mortal could. Stern, warning

Text.Value: I was afraid. Afraid to die. Afraid that I might fail.
Such eddies are unexceptional. Souls arrive and depart your plane with every tide, in circumstances just and unjust.

EditorData.NodeContext: Matter of fact, not interested in these kinds of specifics

Text.Value: If you will not use the orb to end this abomination, then you must find a way to separate Crown and host. When you've done this, you must surrender the Crown of Karsus to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Key info - player quest.

Text.Value: Mystra. Please - I have so much to explain to you.
No.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: Because you had no right to ask that of me. You cast me out, remember?
A great ask indeed. You've given me much to think on - as you always did.
I owe you no explanation. Not after how you've treated me.
So that's what you're scared of. With the Crown of Karsus reforged, I could take control of the Karsite Weave.
If it does not crush you, I will.

EditorData.NodeContext: Here we glimpse the true, unimaginable power of Mystra. She's still in control of herself, but her anger should be palpable.

Text.Value: I understand now why you asked what you did. I should use the orb, and ensure Karsus' powers are truly destroyed.
I did not come here to suffer a mortal's admonitions. Certainly not yours.

EditorData.NodeContext: restrained, but taking no nonsense

Text.Value: You can do this, Gale. Standing up to a goddess is... daunting, but you'll be glad once it's over.
Go on, Gale - see what Mystra has to say for herself. She was never deserving of your worship, anyway.

EditorData.NodeContext: Encouraging  Gale. 'Standing up to a goddess' = SH has turned from Shar. 'see what Mystra...' = SH loyal to Shar (Mystra is typically not a popular goddess with Shar worshippers)

Text.Value: Because I have someone else to live for.
And you believe you have the right to such an understanding?

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of an eyebrow raise - is this a sign of Gale's same old hubris?

Text.Value: Very well. The next time we meet, I'll be bringing you the Crown.
Well? Go on, then - it's rude to keep a goddess waiting.
It was, more than you ever realised.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not letting him off easily

Text.Value: Eh... the first step is difficult, of course. Minsc could throw you in, if you prefer?
It always did. Though the ones we shared were far sweeter than those you've tasted recently.

EditorData.NodeContext: Alluding to the wider plot of the story - that Gale's recently been infected with a tadpole etc. Not overly nostalgic here - she's invoking the 'sweetness' in comparison to the recent chaos Gle's endured, not because she's remembering the sweetness herself

Text.Value: I see you lost your manners, along with the greatest of your gifts.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not really rising to it, but the slightest hint of an eyebrow raise. She's here for more important things that such bickering.

Text.Value: Then why did you strip me of my abilities? I could have put things right.
Speak your mind, Gale. Let go of that weight you have been carrying for Mystra.

EditorData.NodeContext: Encouraging.

Text.Value: You're one to talk. How many innocents were you prepared to sacrifice if I detonated the orb?
With each day that passes, the elder brain threatens to become a new kind of god, its worshippers a scourge of soulless illithids.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hinting at the fact the elder brain will soon evolve, becoming free of the dead three's control. A terrible vision for the future.

Text.Value: When that time comes, call on me in those final moments and I will ensure those close to you are safe from harm.

EditorData.NodeContext: Key info - this gives the player the chance to save their companions before blowing up the brain. A sincere promise from Mystra.

Text.Value: You draw a false conclusion.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: So be it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line

Text.Value: No thanks to you. I wasn't expecting a summons, but then you did always prefer things on your terms.
Yes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contingency line
